NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Had he bid 3S, we really would have had a problem. I think 3S is aggressive at unfavorable vulnerability, but certainly possible. At any other vulnerability, including both vul, I would bid 3S with his hand. At unfavorable vul, you can make a case for either 2S or 3S. 3S is down 3 or 4, so it does not work well if we double. But we might not. |
PG| ***** 54 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|That actually brings up one other interesting point. If it had gone 1C-3S, most people play double there by Elizabeth is negative  as do I. But Marty Bergen recommends another convention, which happens to work real well on this hand. It is called a "Thrump Double." It says, "partner, there is a good possibility we have 3N if you have a spade stopper"  which is the perfect bid for Elizabeth's hand over 3S. Bergen recommends negative doubles through 3C, and doubles of 3D, 3H, and 3S as Thrump Doubles. His booklet on modern doubles has more details.|
