^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, we discussed these last week, but let's go over 4 way transfers again. If you play 2S is a transfer to clubs and 2N is a transfer to diamonds, the NT opener has some options--hence it is called "pre-accept." Over 2S, there are 2 bids he can make, 2N or 3C. Most people play that 2N means the NT opener likes clubs (has 3+ to the A, K, or Q) and 3C means he does not like clubs (denies holding a good club suit). |
