NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|However, some reverse the meaning as Elizabeth apparently does where 3C means the NT bidder likes clubs, and 2N means he does not. Similarly, over 2D, the standard way to play is that 3C by the NT opener shows 3+ diamonds to an honor, and 3D says NT opener does not have good diamonds. Again, you can reverse those meanings as well if you choose. I prefer the standard meaning. BTW, all those bids are alertable.|
