NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So, if playing standard 4-Way transfers with this hand I would bid 2N. The reason being that you want the NT bidder to play the hand. With bad clubs it is more likely you want to play in clubs. So, by bidding 3C with bad clubs, the NT bidder is declarer. Regardless, here I am playing what Elizabeth plays which is the reverse of standard and bid 3C.|
